GateDocument.TextWithNodes: CALL FOR PAPERS International Symposium on Database Technology & Software Engineering , WEB and Cooperative Systems The symposium takes place in conjunction with INTERSYMP 2000 , the 12 th International Conference on System Research , Informatics and Cybernetics . The symposium will be held from August 1 to August 4 , 2000 in Baden- Baden , Germany . The symposium provides a unique international forum for discussions of possible synergistic effects and alternating impacts of Database Technology & Software Engineering with the purpose to build flexible , scalable and well maintainable large , distributed and cooperative information systems , offering information definition and manipulation functionality through the WEB . We invite researchers and practitioners to exchange opinions and provide ideas on how to make a step forward in designing , realizing and maintaining the aforementioned systems from an overall systems' point of view . That includes thinking about directions of Database and Software Engineering research . We formulate as a hypothesis for discussions , that Database Technology and Software Engineering have to learn from each other , or more strongly said , have to "re-use" each other to approach the aforementioned challenges . We invite submissions of quality papers describing original ideas and insights associated with the subject of the symposium . We also welcome papers to identify unsolved problems in the scope of the symposiums' subject . Special sessions will be organized to demonstrate empirical and experimental work on the subject . We do n't limit ourselves to a list of themes . In addition , a special session is planned about a particular application domain : sustainable and safe urban environments . Here , we invite submissions which discuss the pre-conditions and opportunities to support the design , realization and maintenance of information systems which will be able to support the development of sustainable and safe environments . Abstract submission : Participants who wish to present a paper are requested to submit an abstract ( up to 200 words ) as soon as possible , but no later than February the 15 th , 2000 . Notification of acceptance : All submitted papers will be refereed . Notification of acceptance will be sent to authors by March the 6 th , 2000 . Full paper submission : The full-paper , not to exceed 8 single-spaced typed pages , has to be submitted by March the 30 th , 2000 . Submissions can be sent via e-mail to : intersymp @ no . hm . qjyw ( as Word or Postscript file ) or in paper form to : Delft University of Technology Faculty of Information Technology and Systems Prof . Dr . - Ing . habil . W . Gerhardt Zuidplantsoen 4 PO Box 356 , 2600 AJ Delft The Netherlands . Electronic submission is preferred . The layout guidelines are to be found on the Web site of the symposium as of February the 1 st ( http : / / is . twi . tudelft . nl / intersymp-dbse ) . Publishing : The selected submissions will be scheduled for presentation and published in the Conference Proceedings . Outstanding quality papers will be selected for publishing in a book , published by The International Institute for Advanced Studies in Systems Research and Cybernetics . Chairs : Symposium chair : Mrs . W . Gerhardt- Haeckl Co-chairs : Mr . J . van Katwijk , Mr . M . Jenks .
